* Read Separation of Concerns
  - Kind of read: DataObject, KeyValueObject, Key, LargestKeyLessThan, KeyRange - Base Class
  - Strategy for retransmissions - Mixin
  - Strategy for selecting Data targets vs MetadataOnly - Mixin
  - read(DataObjectPtr)
  - read(KeyValueObjectPtr)
  - read(KeyValueObjectPtr, Key) ... KeyRange(min, max), LargetsKeyLessThan(key)
  - read[T](ReadDriver[T]): T
  
  * Maybe add a distinct read method for each read type
     - Returns a future to the appropriate type.
     - Other read() methods immediately fail with AlreadyCalled error
     - Avoids modification of constructor arguments (which is a nice bonus)
     - Top-level promise is promise: Promise[ObjectState]
        - Different reads return different kinds of state
     
  * Reads are either Data or Update-based. 
     - KeyValue reads EITHER return the update set explicitly OR return the full data (from which the updates can be derived)
     - Which makes KeyValue reads just plan "reads"
     - Key-specific reads throw an exception if the object pointer is not a KeyValueObjectPointer
     - Non-Data key-value reads just need a separate set of cases for how to decode the data once a consistent threshold is
       achieved. Won't even need separate subclasses, just a ReadType enum put into the read request
     - KeyValue Data for ReadType
        - FullObject - (null, Raw Data) *** This works for DataObjects as well
        - ByteRange - (min,max) *** DUDE!
        - Key - (updateSet, metadata + ida-encoded value | null)
        - LargetsKeyLessThan (updateSet, key + metadata + ida-encoded value | null)
        - KeyRange (updateSet, [key + metadat + ida-encoded value] | null)
        


